Summaria F(1), Lucci V, Mustilli M.

Author information:
(1)Interventional Cardiology, Policlinico Casilino;

Due to the ageing population and raised life expectancy, elderly patients are 
increasingly referred for percutaneous coronary intervention (PCI) during acute 
coronary syndromes (ACS). Bleeding complications are not infrequent during ACS, 
occurring in 2-5% of patients with prognostic and economic consequences. In 
particular, periprocedural bleeding and vascular complications are associated 
with worse clinical outcome, prolonged hospital stay and increased short- and 
